I think you get my point.. I&#039;m not asking for &quot;more lethality&quot; on the 3 items we have, im asking for more options. Give assassins more tools. You didn&#039;t need to rework Assassins to begin with, if you thought they were binary maybe you should&#039;ve looked at their item options first.  Every other class has various item choices in their class to do their job (granted support items are fairly weak and i won&#039;t argue that, the point is they have more options)

Stop favoring your ADC fantasies and do whats right for the game. Make lethality melee only and at make at leasttttttttttt 3 more freaking lethality items to chose from. If you&#039;re worried about how champions like {{champion:236}} {{champion:202}} etc are going to be after that change, then maybe you need to make more items like {{item:3508}}  that cater towards them. An entire class was reworked into a pile of shit for the ADCs who wanted to split push alone past 20 mins. Blows my mind.

This isn&#039;t rocket science, and I don&#039;t have to be a game designer to figure out that lack of item choices is a HUGE reason why assassins were/are where they&#039;re at.
